Biography

George Edward Parkes was born at Broadwinsor, Dorset, England on 10th February 1893,[1] [2] [3] the son of Edward Thomas Parkes & Mary Jane Young.

George Parkes emigrated to the United States of America in 1910 and was naturalized in 1915.[4]

On 5th June 1917 George Parkes, age 24, of Meeker, Colorado, completed his Registration Card for the United States World War I Draft.[2]

George Edward Parkes married Nellie Ardell Warren 9th July 1919, in Meeker, Rio Blanco, Colorado, USA. [5]

On 27th April 1942 George Parkes, age 49, of Meeker, Rio Blanco, Colorado, completed his Registration Card for the United States World War II Draft. His physical appearance was noted as being white, 5 feet 8 inches tall; weighing 160; with gray eyes; gray hair & a ruddy complexion.[2]

George Edward Parkes died 8th November 1983 [6] in Meeker, Rio Blanco, Colorado, USA & was laid to rest at the Highland Cemetery, Meeker, Rio Blanco, Colorado, USA.[7]
